animal.description:
The first thing you will notice is that he is very handsome. He loves to play chase, do zoomies, and play with his Kong toy.  He invents games, like keep away when my husband calls him to put him in his kennel.  He will play bow, zip around you and jump up and down to get a few more minutes of your time.

Someone invested a lot of love and time with Kade when he was younger but failed to teach him good  citizenship skills and basic obedience.  This means, at times, when playing, he will put your arm or hand in his mouth and apply a little too much force but he is not trying to hurt you. He just gets a little too excited.   His saving grace is that he very smart and loves to learn and please you.

When we let him out of his kennel, he goes out immediately.  When he comes back in we run him through some of the basic commands and reward him with treats.  Then, when possible, we go back to normal household duties and he follows us around like a good dog should.  What I am trying to say is that he is a little rough around the edges but with a little time and positive training methods, he is going to be a great dog.

Kade is very special and in the right home he will blossom into a great dog, a once in a lifetime dog for some lucky family.

P. S.  Kade is being fostered by a dog trainer with over 40 years experience.

If you would like to be considered for adoption, please complete the adoption questionnaire on our website www.heartsofgoldpitrescue.com.

animal.description: Hello! I'm Dan the Man, a handsome Bloodhound that will have you howling with glee when you see me! Like other scent hounds, I do enjoy sniffing out my surroundings while on my walks. I am a bit strong on the leash, but I'm young so I'll probably slow down some as I get older and with daily exercise. I came from the middle of Virginia where hound dogs like me are popular -- perhaps, I went chasing after a coon or something and got lost? Who knows? But, now, I'm ready for a new home, a place where I can share all the love I have to give my new owner -- and let me tell you that's a lot! I'm just an affectionate kind of guy, so this homeless stuff just ain't for me! So if you're looking for a hound dog to share some lovin' with, choose me!!! Dan will do best with an experienced dog owner.This dog can only be adopted within the Washington DC metro area

animal.description:
Ladybelle has been waiting for such a long time to be discovered since coming to us in the summer of 2019 as a stray. She was adopted briefly, but returned when the adopter simply changed their mind. She is about 5 1/2 years old and a shelter is nowhere for Ladybelle. She is very anxious while in a kennel, but once she's away from the hub-bub, Ladybelle turns into a calm, relaxed girl that wants nothing more than to get lots of attention from you, take a walk, and run and play. She has lots of energy and she's very silly and goofy. She sits perfectly when asked and takes treats very gently, and she's a big fan of flopping on her back to get a bellyrub. Ladybelle gets along with most larger dogs so if you have one, bring them in to meet her. She needs a cat-free home though. Ladybelle sure would just love to finally have a family of her own! File#29148 8/8/19 Call 609-693-1900 or email: office@ahsppz.org for an appointment to meet Ladybelle.

If interested please visit our Forked River Shelter. We are open Mon. - Fri. from 12:00 P. M. - 6:00 P. M.; and Sat. & Sun. 12:00 P. M. - 5:00 P. M. for directions call 609-693-1900. There is an adoption donation required. The society cannot accept personal checks but we do accept Visa, MC, AE, Discover and cash. As part of our adoption process, we must have proof of residency. Homeowners must show proof of ownership; landlord approval is required for renters before an adoption can be approved.And as always we thank you for your kindness in opening your heart & home to a Society orphan.

Dexter is a good looking 1yr old cattle dog mix he was transferred in from another shelter when they were out of space and he was out of time.

He's a bit on the timid side around people that he doesn't know but will warm up quickly if you just take your time. He has been mixed with other dogs but cab be selective and bossy. Dexter needs a home with a dog savvy person who is willing to spend some time helping hm adjust to new people. We think he would do best in a home with kids 8yrs of age and over.

Dogs are generally tested with dogs of their own size; and dog meets with the resident dogs are always encouraged. Our cat test should be used as a general purpose screening only to rule out overt aggression; we always recommend caution when introducing dogs to cats in the home. Recommendation on suitability of placement with children by their ages is based on behavioral observations including energy level and response to body handling. We never recommend leaving young children unsupervised with dogs, and we cannot guarantee the behavior of dogs with children, other pets or cats. Behavior evaluations should be considered as a snapshot of the behavior of the dog at this point in time; SCPR believes all dog families need to be prepared to invest time and energy into training as well as provide common sense management of their new dog. We always encourage family to do some research on the breeds or mixes of breeds prior to adoption as many can have some unique characteristics that may or may not fit into their families. For more information about this dog or any others at our Shelter, please visit www.doitforthedogs.com. We are the Second Chance Pet Rescue in Grove, OK. 918-786-7630. You can email us at doitorthepets@gmail.com.

animal.description: Maple is about 9 years old. This poor girl has not had the best start in life and we would really like to find her happily ever after. She was running as a stray in Flint and a local rescue managed to secure her. It is apparent she was used for breeding and was even still full of milk when found. We are guessing that she was tossed outside when she was no longer “useful” to them. She is such a sweet, loving girl. She was in pretty rough shape  when she was found. She does fine with the dogs in her foster home but it took us awhile to get there. It took a lot of training and positive reinforcement. She does not do well meeting new dogs as she tends to be confrontational. For this reason, we feel she would do best as an only dog. She does great with cats. She does tend to be very fearful about being outside by herself. She will go out and take care of her business but is a bit frantic to be let back in. Although we are working on it, she is not that great on a leash. She would do best with a fenced yard. She tends to have separation anxiety in new situations so does take time to adjust to a new setting and routine. Maple is spayed, HW checked and is up to date on shots. For more information, please contact tamjov@aol.com.

animal.description:
Zion could be described as a diamond in the rough. He is a special guy and the class clown, once he knows you. He had some traumatic experiences in his past that caused him to be nervous in some situations and with new people. He is extremely food motivated and he has worked hard with his caregivers and has blossomed into who he was meant to be. He still takes a little time to trust, but once you have gained it, you are in for life. 
Once Zion is comfortable with his people, he enjoys walks, golf cart rides, car rides, playing with his stuffed toys, swimming in the pool at the dog park and enjoying a good hang out session on the couch. He approaches life with boundless optimism and loves to play with his people when he is comfortable.

animal.description:
Twiggy is a very sweet tempered, nice dog. She was a dog that ran in the woods with her sister for some time, a stray, she was completely unsocialized and had to be trapped in order to get her to the vet to spay her. When she came to our shelter she would not walk at all and had to be carried from her indoor kennel to her outdoor enclosure. It took many months before she was able to be walked on a leash and felt comfortable here. She is still very timid and will shy away from anything she isn't familiar with. 
She needs to have a companion dog her age to play with and that will give her more confidence; she needs a fenced in yard with a 5' fence or higher. She is a dog that is on the small side of large and over 50lbs. She looks smaller in the pictures here than she actually is. She's slender. 
Her disposition is good, although fearful she is not aggressive, she is fine with children, she is not food agresssive. 
She will require a lot of patience and months of getting used to a new environment. She will not be a dog that you can walk down a residential street, at least not at this point. She will just sit down and not move if she's uncomfortable.  It took her over 6 months to get used to the shelter environment. 
She doesn't really like being in a kennel, but she's fairly housetrained, at least if kept in a room, she doesn't have accidents. She's not high energy, but she does enjoy being outside and will run away if let off leash like most hounds, she chases deer and wildlife.

Adoption fee is $150
She is spayed, heartworm tested, vaccinated, wormed, flea and tick treated
animal.name: Twiggy

animal.description:
Stryker is an adult border collie mix that is looking for a new home. He loves to play with tennis balls and run around the yard.  He is learning to sit when petted, but sometimes he gets so excited for a hug that he will jump up on people.  He is crate trained and can be in one for quite a long time with no accidents or barking.  He is unpredictable around other dogs and would be best as an only dog with his own fenced yard.  He would not be a good candidate to take to dog parks where he would be interacting with lots of new dogs he didn't know.  He is sweet with people.
Stryker is looking for a forever family to call his own. His adoption fee is $200, which includes neuter surgery and vaccinations (parvo/distemper and rabies.) If you would like to meet this dog, please email us: scfourpaws@hotmail.com or leave a message @ 435/752-3534. Please be patient with us getting back to you as we are all volunteers with full-time jobs. Thanks for your interest in this wonderful dog!!

animal.description:
Oscar is an unusual looking dog with such a cute face! We think he might be a cattle dog/Aussie/kelpie mix.  He almost looks like he has a GSD head on a Corgi body!  He is about 2 years old. He seems to be good with other dogs and is happy and smart.  He likes to be around people.  He has a very high pitched bark.  He would love to be a hiking buddy or camping companion.  Oscar is great with other dogs and could spend all day playing. He is very active. He needs a home where he can get lots of exercise.  He could use a job to do.  He is not good with cats.

Oscar is looking for a forever family to call his own. His adoption fee is $200 which includes neuter surgery and vaccinations (parvo/distemper and rabies.) If you would like to meet this dog, please email us: scfourpaws@hotmail.com or leave a message @ 435/752-3534. Please be patient with us getting back to you as we are all volunteers with full-time jobs. Thanks for your interest in this wonderful dog!!

animal.description:
ASTER is a shy, currently FERAL, beautiful pup, being socialized at this time. She gets along well with other dogs, and she is a beloved part of the 'RezQue AVNM' rescue of 50 highway dogs from the Mescalero Reservation in New Mexico. She is learning to trust humans, and being well-nourished, after being found as a starving puppy with her siblings and beautiful mommy.

DOB: 4-15-18
Adoption fee: 225.

Pet introductions are scheduled when adoption applications are approved. 
Submit $25 application fee with your online application now at animalvillagenm.org/adoption-application

To make sure our pets go to wonderful, safe, responsible homes, we introduce our pets to those who have already submitted complete applications, which have been approved. We adopt only to experienced pet guardians with EXCELLENT veterinary histories, based on conversations with your current or past veterinarian(s.). Please do not ask us to make exceptions.

All information ( and applications ) about our adoption process to adopters all over the U.S. is available at AnimalVillageNM.org.
